latestIgtvVideos.title: Our 2020 Sequel Wedding!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
You can have the wedding of your dreams, but just requires perspective. While it was not my full blown initial plan I dreamt of as a little girl, I chose to change my perspective with the new norm given to us. Make a plan, be creative, pivot, cry it out, and NEVER give up...even if it may not the time right now, your time WILL come. 

Best day of our lives. @jjjames226 Thank you @madlovemedia__ for capturing all these precious moments.

latestPosts.caption:
🎓 I thought once I earned the degree, doors would fly open.
I thought employers would see the late nights, the sacrifices, the internships, the passion.
But no one told me this:

✨ Degrees don’t guarantee jobs.
✨ Most roles are filled through relationships, not job boards.
✨ Employers want proof of impact, not just education.
✨ You have to market yourself like a brand, not just submit applications.
✨ Mindset matters — you have to shift from “hire me” to “here’s the value I bring.”

I had to learn the hard way.
That the real work starts after graduation.
That rejection doesn’t mean you’re not enough — it just means your path is still unfolding.

If you’re here right now — discouraged, tired, second-guessing everything —
💛 You’re not alone.
Your degree wasn’t a mistake.
You’re not behind.
You’re becoming.

Tag someone who needs to hear this. And if you’re on this journey too, drop a 💬 below — let’s build together.

#MHAgrad #MPHgrad #MBAgrad #HealthcareLeadership #CareerGrowth #WomenInHealthcare #FirstGenSuccess #JobSearchStruggles #YoureNotAlone

latestPosts.caption:
🎯 5 Tiny Habits That Make a Huge Impact in Your Healthcare Career 💥
It’s the little things that separate the good from the great 👏🏽

Here’s what’s helped me grow faster, feel more fulfilled, and stay aligned with my purpose in healthcare:
1️⃣ Build real connections – your coworkers are your greatest asset
2️⃣ Set monthly goals + share wins with your boss = visibility 💡
3️⃣ Think long-term → stop chasing jobs, start building your career
4️⃣ Track your impact! Keep an ongoing list of accomplishments 📝
5️⃣ Don’t just network—nurture those relationships ❤️

Which one are you already doing? Which one will you try? 👇🏽 #HealthcareCareer #CareerGrowth #HealthLeaders #WomenInHealthcare #CareerTips #HealthcareProfessional
